      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">詩經·小雅·魚藻之什·012.1</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">漸漸之石.1</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>漸漸之石，維其高矣。山川悠遠，維其勞矣。武人東征，不皇朝矣。
漸漸之石，維其卒矣。山川悠遠，曷其沒矣。武人東征，不皇出矣。
有豕白蹢，烝涉波矣。月離于畢，俾滂沱矣。武人東征，不皇他矣。</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>1 Those frowning rocks, —
How high they rise!
Over such a distance of hills and streams,
How toilsome is the march!
The warrior, in charge of the expedition to the east,
Has not a morning’s leisure.</seg>
      </tuv>
